OL,3,CSouthport killer's brother says school
OL,4,Cexpulsion increased his 'isolation'
OL,6,F"By virtue of his studies and his
OL,7,Fdisability, Dion had limited
OL,8,Finteraction with his brother but Dion
OL,9,Fis aware that in addition to police
OL,10,Finvolvement with AR, agencies such as
OL,11,FSocial Services and CAMHS (Child and
OL,12,FAdolescent Mental Health Services)
OL,13,Fwere also involved with his brother.
OL,15,F"Dion, like many others, wishes the
OL,16,Finquiry to explore whether more could
OL,17,Fhave been done by those agencies to
OL,18,Ftry and assist AR and/or whether they
OL,19,Fcould have intervened in such a way as
OL,20,Fto have minimised the prospect of the
OL,21,Fattacks from occurring."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
